1️⃣ HOW RECRUITERS READ A FRESHER RESUME

⚠️ Most recruiters scan a resume in 30–60 seconds.

They usually check:

Education
Skills
Projects
Internships / Certifications
Strengths & extracurriculars
🔹 Ideal Fresher Resume Sections

✅ Name + Contact
✅ Career Objective
✅ Education
✅ Technical Skills
✅ Projects
✅ Certifications
✅ Achievements
✅ Positions of Responsibility

🎯 Strong Career Objective Example
Writing

Motivated engineering student seeking an entry-level opportunity to apply problem-solving, analytical, and technical skills while contributing to organizational growth and continuously learning.

🔹 Projects Matter (Very Important)

HR may ask:

“Explain one project you have done.”

Use this structure:

Problem → What you built → Tools used → Outcome

Example Format
Writing

I worked on a Women Safety Watch App concept focused on sending SOS alerts without internet. The idea was to improve emergency response using offline signaling and location-based alerts.

2️⃣ TOP HR QUESTIONS YOU MUST MASTER
❓ Why should we hire you?

Use 3-point formula:

Skills
Attitude
Contribution
❓ Why our company?

Never say:
❌ “Because it is famous.”

Say:

Writing

I want to join your company because of its learning environment, innovation culture, and the opportunity to grow while contributing meaningfully.

❓ Are you willing to relocate?

Best answer (usually):

“Yes, I am open to relocation based on project and business needs.”

❓ Do you have any questions for us?

Always ask one.

Examples:

What does success look like in this role?
What learning opportunities are available for freshers?
3️⃣ RESUME MISTAKES TO AVOID

❌ Fake skills
❌ Mentioning tools you can’t explain
❌ Long paragraphs
❌ Weak project descriptions
